
[1]litigious

   LITIG'IOUS, a. [L. litigiosus.]

   1. Inclined to judicial contest; given to the practice of contending in
   law; quarrelsome; contentious; applied to persons. a litigious man is a
   bad neighbor and a bad citizen.

   2. Disputable; controvertible; subject to contention; as litigious
   right.

   No fences, parted fields, nor marks nor bounds, distinguish'd acres of
   litigious grounds.
